list.abstract: new是一个英文单词，形容词、名词、副词，作形容词时翻译为“新的，新鲜的；更新的；初见的”，作名词时翻译为“人名；(英)纽”，作副词时翻译为“新近”。
NEW是STL （ Standard Template Library，标准模板库，惠普实验室开发的一系列软件的统称。惠普实验室开发）软件数据的一种。从堆中划分一块区域，动态创建一个类型的数据，最后返回该区域的指针。该数据类型可以是标准数据类型，也可以是用户自定义类型。

yingyinNormal.en: Welcome to the new Panem.
yingyinNormal.zh: 欢迎来到崭新的帕纳姆国。

yingyinNormal.en: It's time I try something new.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是时候我尝试一些新的东西。

yingyinNormal.en: A new tomorrow that starts today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个新的明天即将到来。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, do I fix it or get a new one?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是拿去修呢？还是干脆换把新的？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, new contest. What are you doing?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，来场新的比赛。你要干什么？

yingyinNormal.en: Why didn't we know that? It's a new rule.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们之前怎么不知道？这是一条新的规则。

yingyinNormal.en: Your new curfew is 8:00. God bless America!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你新的最晚回家时间定为八点，愿上帝保佑美国！

yingyinNormal.en: Has new material arrived ahead of schedule?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有新的资料提前到了吗

yingyinNormal.en: Yours for the entire trip. Four new Maybachs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您全程的交通工具，四辆全新的迈巴赫。

yingyinNormal.en: I missed Comic Con and the new Star Trek movie!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我错过了动漫展，连新的《星际迷航》电影也错过啦！

yingyinNormal.en: See, it's not old fish. It's a whole new thing!
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们不再是不新鲜的鱼肉，是崭新的菜！

yingyinNormal.en: I've been out of town all summer. Anything new?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我整个夏天都外出了，有啥新的吗?

yingyinNormal.en: I need the new Harry Potter book for the twins.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要给双胞胎新的《哈里·波特》。

yingyinNormal.en: Which begs the question, who is the new Ant-Man?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那问题就来了，谁是那个新的蚁人？

yingyinNormal.en: Last month, our businesses added 236,000 new jobs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 上个月,我们的经济创造了236,000新的就业岗位。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, Wyatt, on the other hand, that's something new.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过另一方面，怀亚特可是全新的存在。

yingyinNormal.en: It's my new motto. Are they okay? Jeffrey's parents?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是我最新的座右铭，杰弗里的父母没事吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Last month, our businesses created 314,000 new jobs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 上个月，我们的经济创造了314,000个新的就业岗位。

yingyinNormal.en: Every time we've unveiled a new asset, attendance has spiked.
yingyinNormal.zh: 每次我们推出一个新的资产的时候，入场率都会飙升。

yingyinNormal.en: Is that message old or new? Old or new? Old or new?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这则留言是新的还是旧的？新的还是旧的？

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: And <highlight>new</highlight> research suggests that happiness might influence how firms work, too.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新的研究表明，快乐也可能影响公司的运作方式。

examination_example.sentence: A <highlight>new</highlight> study suggests that contrary to most surveys, people are actually more stressed at home than at work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项新的研究表明，与大多数调查相反，人们实际上在家里比在工作中更有压力。

examination_example.sentence: Accommodating this <highlight>new</highlight> world of people in motion will require <highlight>new</highlight> attitudes on both sides of the immigration battle.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 适应这个新的流动人群世界将需要移民战双方的新态度。

examination_example.sentence: They're choosing their home – without actually getting a choice in the matter, said Adam Bailey, real estate attorney based in <highlight>New</highlight> York.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 纽约房地产律师Adam Bailey说，他们正在选择自己的家——实际上在这件事上没有选择。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>New</highlight> York Times is considering ending its print edition partly due to the high cost of operation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 《纽约时报》考虑终止印刷版，部分原因是运营成本高。

examination_example.sentence: There will eventually come a day when The <highlight>New</highlight> York Times ceases to publish stories on newsprint.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 终有一天，《纽约时报》将停止在新闻纸上发表报道。

examination_example.sentence: It can be learned from the last paragraph that young people are curious about <highlight>new</highlight> food.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从上一段可以看出，年轻人对新食物充满好奇。

指物没有变质、清新、有活力或出现不久、少见等；指人无经验等。

examination_example.sentence: It was completed in the state of <highlight>New</highlight> Mexico.

new作形容词时，常与介词to连用，表示“对…不熟悉的”。

正 We are still new to our duties.

new常与the连用，表示“新东西, 新事物”。
示例：It was a good mix of the old and the new.
这是新旧的完美结合。

examination_example.sentence: The debate isn't <highlight>new</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这场辩论并不新鲜。

examination_example.sentence: How do you like your <highlight>new</highlight> flexible working arrangement?

examination_example.sentence: The article says many people tend to assume that innovation just means creating something <highlight>new</highlight>, but actually it's more than that.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这篇文章说，许多人倾向于认为创新只是意味着创造新的东西，但事实上不仅仅如此。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>new</highlight> baby expands the zoo's elephant herd to six.

examination_example.sentence: What does the report say about the birth of the <highlight>new</highlight> baby elephant?

examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近，在一次同事聚会上，有人问我：“最近有什么新鲜事吗?”

examination_example.sentence: Still, the only "<highlight>new</highlight>-to-me" topics that came to mind were my daughter's basketball tournament (锦标赛) .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不过，唯一浮现在我脑海中的“新”话题是我女儿的篮球锦标赛。

examination_example.sentence: Suppose your school is organizing an orientation program to help the freshmen adapt to the <highlight>new</highlight> environment and academic studies.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设你的学校正在组织一个新生适应计划，以帮助新生适应新的环境和学术研究。

word_usage.usage:
new作形容词时，常与介词to连用，表示“对…不熟悉的”。
示例：我们对自己的职责还不熟悉。
误 We are still new with our duties.
正 We are still new to our duties.

new常与the连用，表示“新东西, 新事物”。
示例：It was a good mix of the old and the new.
这是新旧的完美结合。
